# OctoAcme — QA Strategy & Quality Management

## Purpose
Define how quality is ensured across project execution, from acceptance criteria definition through release.

## Quality Principles
- Quality is everyone's responsibility
- Shift left: identify and fix issues early in development
- Automated testing for speed and consistency
- Clear acceptance criteria before development starts
- User acceptance validation before release

## Definition of Done (Quality Component)
Features are complete when:
- [ ] Acceptance criteria are defined and agreed upon
- [ ] Unit tests are written and passing (target: >80% coverage)
- [ ] Code review is complete with at least one approval
- [ ] Integration tests pass in CI/CD
- [ ] Manual QA sign-off is obtained
- [ ] Documentation is updated
- [ ] Performance acceptable (load time, memory, etc.)
- [ ] Security scan passes

## Test Plan Template
- Test Scope: features, components, or modules being tested
- Test Approach: unit, integration, E2E, performance, security
- Test Cases: acceptance criteria mapped to test cases
- Test Data: fixtures or mock data needed
- Test Schedule: when tests run (per-commit, nightly, pre-release)
- Success Criteria: pass rate, coverage targets

## QA Responsibilities by Role
| Phase | QA Lead | Developers | Product Manager | Project Manager |
|-------|---------|-----------|-----------------|-----------------|
| Planning | Define test approach | Estimate testability | Define acceptance criteria | Track QA schedule |
| Development | Review test cases | Write unit tests, participate in code review | Validate acceptance criteria | Identify QA blockers |
| Review | Conduct manual QA | Support QA questions | Validate feature completeness | Report QA progress |
| Release | Quality sign-off | Fix critical issues | Confirm readiness | Manage release timing |

## Defect Triage & Resolution
- **Critical:** Blocks release, fix immediately
- **High:** Impacts core functionality, fix before release or document workaround
- **Medium:** Nice to fix, consider for next release
- **Low:** Minor/cosmetic, backlog for future iteration

## Quality Metrics
- Test coverage percentage
- Defect escape rate (bugs found in production)
- Mean time to resolution (MTTR)
- Release quality (incidents/errors in first week)

## QA Sign-Off Checklist
- [ ] All acceptance criteria tested and passed
- [ ] No critical or high-priority open defects
- [ ] Test coverage meets targets
- [ ] Performance and security checks passed
- [ ] Release notes reviewed for accuracy
- [ ] User documentation validated